---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-25';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Wyreup"
  description="What Wyreup collects, what it doesn't, and how the PRO tier differs from free tools."
>
  <article class="legal">
    <header>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Free tools run entirely on your device.</strong> When you
      use a free tool in the browser or via the CLI / MCP, Wyreup is
      not involved at runtime — your files, parameters, and outputs
      never reach our infrastructure. No accounts, no cookies, no
      analytics, no telemetry.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>PRO tools forward your input to a third-party
      hosted-AI model when you invoke them.</strong> When <strong>you</strong>
      choose a PRO tool and submit an input, the input is routed
      through Wyreup's edge to the model provider (Cloudflare Workers
      AI or our image-model provider) that runs against it. The model —
      not Wyreup — acts on your data. Wyreup is the conduit: we route
      the request, deduct the credit, and return the model's response
      to you. We do not retain the input or output beyond the request.
      We do log metadata (which tool ran, when, file name) for your run
      history.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>You decide what gets sent.</strong> You choose which
      tools to invoke and which inputs to submit. You are responsible
      for confirming you have the right to submit the input and for
      whatever you do with the output. See section 5 of the
      <a href="/legal/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>

    <h3>For free tools</h3>
    <p><strong>Nothing.</strong> Free tools never reach our backend.</p>

    <h3>For PRO accounts</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email address.</strong> Used to deliver your API key and account notices.</li>
      <li><strong>SHA-256 hash of each API key.</strong> The raw key is never stored — it's delivered once via email and shown once at creation.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Run history metadata.</strong> Tool ID, credits consumed,
        timestamp, and the file name you submitted (not the file content).
        We use this only to show you your own history.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Credit ledger.</strong> Purchases, spends, refunds — for
        billing transparency and to compute your balance.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Connection IP</strong> for the <code>/api/account/create</code>
        endpoint, retained for 24 hours to enforce rate limits. Never linked
        to your account thereafter.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What we never store</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>File contents — your files are forwarded through Wyreup to the model provider and discarded on our side immediately after the request returns.</li>
      <li>Output contents — the model's response is returned to you and not retained on our side.</li>
      <li>Card numbers — handled by Lemon Squeezy, never by Wyreup.</li>
      <li>Plain-text API keys.</li>
      <li>Analytics, fingerprints, third-party tracking, or advertising cookies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We set a single cookie, <code>__Host-wyreup_session</code>, after you
      activate your API key in the browser. It's HttpOnly, Secure,
      SameSite=Lax, and expires after 24 hours. It is strictly necessary
      for sign-in and is exempt from consent requirements under most
      regimes (including the GDPR ePrivacy Directive). We set no other
      cookies.
    </p>

    <h2>Subprocessors</h2>
    <p>
      When you invoke a PRO tool, your input is forwarded through the
      providers listed below. Under GDPR/CCPA we are required to
      disclose categories of recipients; we name them specifically
      here for transparency where we can. If we change a provider, we
      will update this list promptly. The actual processing of your
      input is performed by the third-party model provider, not by
      Wyreup.
    </p>
    <p>When you invoke a PRO tool, your input is forwarded through:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — site hosting, edge compute (Pages
        Functions), database (D1, in the Eastern North America region),
        and AI inference (Workers AI). See Cloudflare's
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>An external image-model provider</strong> — hosts the
        models that power the image PRO tools (background removal,
        upscaling). The provider receives the image you submit but,
        under our agreement with them, does not retain inputs or
        outputs beyond the request. We may change providers from time
        to time; the current provider's name and privacy policy are
        available on request at <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong> — merchant of record for credit
        purchases. Receives your billing info (name, billing address,
        payment instrument). Never sees your tool inputs or API keys.
        See Lemon Squeezy's <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Zoho (ZeptoMail)</strong> — transactional email delivery.
        Receives your email address and the message body (welcome key,
        account notices). See Zoho's
        <a href="https://www.zoho.com/privacy.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>You can, at any time:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access:</strong> view your run history and account at <a href="/account">wyreup.com/account</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Export:</strong> email <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong> for a JSON export of everything we have on you.</li>
      <li><strong>Delete:</strong> email <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong> to close your account; unused credits are refunded per the <a href="/legal/refund">refund policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Rectify:</strong> change your email by emailing <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong> from the address on file.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If you are in the EU/UK, you also have the right to lodge a
      complaint with your local supervisory authority.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      Wyreup is not directed at children under 13 (or under 16 in the EU).
      We do not knowingly collect their information.
    </p>

    <h2>Data transfers and edge routing</h2>
    <p>
      Wyreup is operated from Indiana, United States, but Wyreup itself
      runs as an edge-compute application on Cloudflare's global
      network. Your data does not see Wyreup-owned servers in any
      meaningful sense — when you invoke a PRO tool, the request is
      handled by whichever Cloudflare data center is nearest to you (or
      to the routing path), forwarded to the model provider (Cloudflare
      Workers AI or our image-model provider), and the response is
      returned to you. The model provider in turn may operate in any
      region where it has infrastructure, including but not limited to
      regions outside the United States.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Wyreup does not select the region for any individual
      request, and we do not guarantee which country a given request
      will pass through.</strong> If your data is subject to
      data-residency, cross-border-transfer, or sovereignty
      requirements — GDPR Chapter V transfer rules, UK data-residency
      requirements, healthcare or government sectoral regimes,
      financial-services egress restrictions, or any equivalent — it
      is your responsibility to independently verify whether routing
      through Cloudflare's network and the relevant model provider is
      permitted under the rules that apply to you. See section 6 of
      the <a href="/legal/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Free tools are not affected — they run entirely on your device
      and never touch Cloudflare's network or any third-party model.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy. Material changes will be noted by updating
      the "Last updated" date and by emailing your account address where
      appropriate.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy questions or rights requests: <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong>.<br />
      Security disclosures (vulnerability reports, suspected key
      compromise): <strong>security@wyreup.com</strong>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4) var(--space-12);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl, 28px);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-2);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal ul {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }
  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92em;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 1px 4px;
  }
  .meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
